body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Secure Motors. My name is Gabriel Turner. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Kathleen Gray. Can you please provide me with the make and model of your vehicle?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's a four door sedan.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, and can you also confirm the last four digits of your VIN number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, the last four digits are nine one two three.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Kathleen Gray. Is there anything else you'd like to share with us today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. I appreciate your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for contacting Secure Motors, Kathleen Gray. We will look into the security concern related to the dealership. Have a wonderful day!

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, I already feel relieved. Goodbye.
